–1380","1275–1347":"1275–1347","1305":"1305","1347":"1347","1302":"1302","1322":"1322","1375":"1375","1275":"1275","1362":"1362","abt 1362":"about 1362","1380":"1380","Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom","Swinfen and Packington, Lichfield, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Packington, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom","Sutton Cheynell, Leics, Eng.":"Leicestershire, England, United Kingdom","Swynfen Staffordshire England":"Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom","Swinfen Packington, Lichfield, Staffordshire, England":"Lichfield, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom","Swinfen and Packington, Lichfield, Staffordshire, England":"Packington, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom","nameMeanings":[{"name":"Aust","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of American Family Names © Patrick Hanks 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Some characteristic forenames:  German Dietmar, Erwin, Gerhard, Gunter, Jurgen, Kurt, Rudi, Willi.","German: from a shortened form of the personal name   August   or   Augustin  .","English: habitational name from Aust, Gloucestershire, whose name derives from Latin <i>augustus</i> ‘consecrated, majestic, venerable’ in a Vulgar Latin and Brittonic Celtic form <i>agust-</i>, with possible reference to the Roman Second Legion (Augusta), stationed at Caerleon on Usk, just across the Severn from Aust, in 75 C.E."],"variants":[{"name":"August","meanings":["German and English: from the personal name <i>August</i>, from Latin <i>Augustus</i> ‘consecrated, majestic, venerable’ (see   Augustus  )."]}]},{"name":"Swynfen","type":"LAST","attribution":"Dictionary of Family Names in Britain and Ireland © University of the West of England 2016","meanings":["English: locative name from Swinfen (Staffs)."],"variants":[{"name":"Swiffen","meanings":["English: possibly a variant of   Swinfen   with loss of /n/ before a fricative consonant."]}]},{"name":"John","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["As a boy's name this represents a revival of Middle English <i>Jan</i>, a by‐form of   John  , or an adoption of the common European form with this spelling. As a girl's name it is a short form of names such as   Janet   and   Janice ."],"variants":[]},{"name":"II","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["Short form of   Violet  ,   Vivien  , or   Vivian ."],"variants":[{"name":"Vivien","meanings":["Earlier generally taken as a variant of the boy's name   Vivian  , but now also rarely used for boys. This spelling was quite common in Old French. Its use as a girl's name in the English-speaking world was influenced by  Tennyson's  Merlin and Vivien (  1859 ). This name, from Arthurian legend, may represent an altered form of a Celtic name (perhaps akin to the Irish Gaelic name <i>Béibhinn</i> ‘white lady’, pronounced ‘bee-<b>veen</b>’). The actress  Vivien Leigh  (  1913–67 ) was christened <i>Vivian</i>."]},{"name":"Violet","meanings":["From the name of the flower (Old French <i>violette</i>, Late Latin <i>violetta</i>, a diminutive of <i>viola</i>). This was one of the earliest flower names to become popular in Britain, being used as early as  1700  and becoming well established in the 19th century, although it is now somewhat out of favour."]},{"name":"Vivian","meanings":["Originally a boy's name, from an Old French form of the Latin name <i>Vivianus</i> (probably a derivative of <i>vivus</i> ‘alive’), but now more frequent as a girl's name. The name was borne by a 5th-century bishop of Saintes in western France, remembered for protecting his people during the invasion of the Visigoths."]}]}],"lifeSummary":"John II Aust Swynfen was born in 1302, in Packington, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom as the son of John I Auste Swinfen - Lord of Swynfen. He had at least 2 sons and 1 daughter with Matilda Freford. He died in 1380, in his hometown, at the age of 78."},"et":{"1302–1380":"1302–1380","1305–1380":"1305–1380","1322–1375":"1322–1375","1362–Male":"1362–Surnud","–1380":"–1380","1275–1347":"1275–1347","1305":"1305","1347":"1347","1302":"1302","1322":"1322","1375":"1375","1275":"1275","1362":"1362","abt 1362":"umbes 1362","1380":"1380","Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Swinfen and Packington, Lichfield, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Packington, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Sutton Cheynell, Leics, Eng.":"Leicestershire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Swynfen Staffordshire England":"Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Swinfen Packington, Lichfield, Staffordshire, England":"Lichfield, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Swinfen and Packington, Lichfield, Staffordshire, England":"Packington, Staffordshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1302–1380":"1302–1380","1305–1380":"1305–1380","1322–1375":"1322–1375","1362–Male":"1362–Kuollut","–1380":"–1380","1275–1347":"1275–1347","1305":"1305","1347":"1347","1302":"1302","1322":"1322","1375":"1375","1275":"1275","1362":"1362","abt 1362":"noin 1362","1380":"1380","Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Swinfen and Packington, Lichfield, Staffordshire, England, United Kingdom":"Packington, Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Sutton Cheynell, Leics, Eng.":"Leicestershire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Swynfen Staffordshire England":"Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Swinfen Packington, Lichfield, Staffordshire, England":"Lichfield, Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta","Swinfen and Packington, Lichfield, Staffordshire, England":"Packington, Staffordshire, Englanti, Yhdistynyt kuningaskunta"},"fr":{"1302–1380":"1302–1380","1305–1380":"1305–1380","1322–1375":"1322–1375","1362–Male":"1362–Décédé","–1380":"–1380","1275–1347":"1275–1347","1305":"1305","1347":